Date: 0/0/1876
Source: NZ Parliamentary Debates
Author:
Vol / Page: 20/73
Edition:
Quote: I am not aware that Ministers of the Crown have been in the habit of bringing before Parliament what took place at a meeting of their supporters. It is supposed that these things are done secretly; and if it is parliamentary to refer to such a thing as a caucus meeting, I can only assume we are getting sort of Americanized in some of our proceedings and this serves as the first step in making us acquainted with what are called caucuses and rings.
